Title: Standing Propane Patio Heater Wheels Anti-tilt Hammered Adjustable Steel Bronze
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: Mr Heater Big Buddy Portable Propane Radiant 3 Heat Settings Indoor 18,000 BTU
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Title: Dyson AM04 Hot + Cool Heater/Table Fan
Reviews: ["Because of  a Great Price offer  so I thought Id try The Dyson AM04as I have nothing but praise for their Vacuum cleaners.   Its not big enough to really cool off a room and its too big to be a desk fan so just keep dimensions in mind when ordering.I like the fan as a Heater more then I like it as a Cool Fan but that's my opinion.I do like that its able to be both a hot and cool fan depending on time of year in one machine.if you think because its a dyson and its expensive you will get a Heater that Burns you or a Cool Fan that will Blast Artic air until you are content, you might be setting yourself up for disappointment.           If sheer Blasting power of either hot air or cool air is what you seek my opinion is Dyson falls Short and cheaper models are available, with more power.I enjoy the bladeless design and having both in one machine and for the price I'm happy!", 'This product does a great job in a living room on those hot summer days and cold winter nights. The heating function works exceptionally well and automatically holds the room temperature. The fan operation is true to Dyson standards and creates a smooth calm flow of air throughout the room. I definitely am glad that i purchased this unit used since a new unit costs about $400. Way too much for a fan. I am defiantly happy i purchased this second hand.', 'I have always wanted a Dyson hybrid fan and heater and when I saw an opportunity to get it for less than $300, even at refurbished condition, I had to just get it. It IS supposed to be refurbished by a Dyson certified dealer so I felt I could trust its condition to be satisfactory and safe. So far, the fan has been great in circulating air, albeit a little noisy even at its low setting, but it IS a fan and to be expected. I have not experienced using the heat setting yet, although I have tested it to be working so hopefully it will be sufficient for the winter months. Has a few dings, but its cosmetic and all I really care about is that it is safe to use, especially around children.', "Dyson produces high quality products that can have a problem once in a while so the company reworks the product and sells it at a more attractive price. I've had the hot and cool fan just a few weeks and it's working just fine. It's especially quiet, heats up and cools down quickly, and the remote makes it really easy to control. I also like not needing a separate fan and heater.", 'Fan works great, the remote makes it better. The heater is not as warm as most electric heaters, but will warm things if left on for a while. Saves having two separate devices. Was refurbished, but looks good and nicely packaged for shipment.', 'We used it on our sail boat.  So far just the summer.  It appears the heater works better than the cool.  but it is way better that not having!', "This fan/heater moves a lot of air in fan mode, and heats up quickly (however it takes about 20 seconds for the heating element and fan to switch on once the heater is engaged).It's probably a little quieter than most fans that move this much air, but it's not as whisper quiet as the new Dyson models. Even on the the lowest fan setting it could be considered a good sleeping noise maker. As advertised mine did not come with a remote, but I ordered one off the Dyson website and it works perfectly. I'm a big fan of this fan. 4/5 stars only because it's a little louder than I expected, but aside from that I LOVE IT.", 'I also have a brand new version so I can compare versions that are 5 apart and honestly there is very little difference from one to the other. I think we should all keep that in mind when considering the possibility of getting a newer version.  It is amazing how close to each other they are in function. Truly amazing.', 'High quality materials, high performance.', "I have wanted this Dyson fan for 6 years,but couldn't afford it. When I saw it on sale I didn't  hesitate and ordered  it. I am extremely  thankful  it came  early,as we were hit with a heat wave that lasted ten days at 110 degrees."]

Title: Infrared Wall Heater
Reviews: ["As a secondary heating source this is the best I've found. Title: Mr. Heater 18,000 BTU Propane Cabinet Heater
Reviews: ['I\'ve wrestled with the heating options for my sun room since my wife and daughter through out my "old" kerosene heaters.  I considered the small propane table top heaters but my wife nixed that idea.  The typical outdoor 8 foot high propane heaters would have probably have drawn to much oxygen from the 13\' X 20\' sun room.  As I searched for other heating options, I came across this heater that stored a 20 lb. tank and made it look aesthetically pleasing.  It provides the right amount of heat for various atmospheric conditions!', 'We use the heater to supplement our fuel oil furnace. Works great to give a shot of heat while maintaining an overall lower temperature while we are gone', 'We got the heater shortly before Christmas 2017 here in Texas. Same day it arrived we had a freeze. Heater was installed in a converted barn and temp got up to about 75 in 15min or so. We have been using it for about a week now in below freezing temps with no issues other than it takes a few clicks to get the pilot to light. With all 3 burners going I pointed my temp gun at the front. My gun only goes to 1,000 deg and the heater is over that.', "Great heater for my garage/workshop.  The heater puts out enough heat to warm up my 24' x x24' garage on a cold winters day (in Michigan).  With it's 3 settings (Lo, Med & Hi) I start on Hi to raise the temp, then I set it to Lo to maintain temp.  I like the idea that the LP tank is built into the heater (instead of a separate tank and extension hose).  It makes the heater easy to roll around the shop and set it where the heat is needed.  I've had no issues with it not starting or operating properly.All in all, this is one great little portable heater.  I'd definitely but it again.", 'It is exactly what we needed. Works great and heats fast. Great product.', 'It is used every day sometimes three or four times to take the chill off in my 14 x 30 cabin. Fifteen min. or so is all it takes even when it is 12 fa outside. Wish I had it last year. Thanks Mr Heater !', "I've had this heater for a month now and have used it in my garage. It works great in the garage even when it was 20 degrees outside. On high, I have to sit about 2 feet away or I start to get too hot. I normally turn it to medium setting once I start getting hot. It takes about 5 minutes to get up to full heat, and very minimum fumes.  I'm still using my first tank of gas! I love this heater!", 'This heater holds a 20-pound propane tank. It does a good job of providing radiant heat. The pilot light ignites automatically, making the heater easy to use. I am happy with it, although I have used it only three times so far.', 'fast shipping and heats up the area we needed it for quit fast', 'Works great, Gives off perfect amount of heat with the three settings.Recommended to anyone that is cold, and on a budget for heat.I first learned of these while in Greece in the navy. we used them over winter, where the climate was not so cold, but, you still needed something for quick heat to take the chill off.']

Title: Mr Heater Big Buddy Portable Propane Radiant 3 Heat Settings Indoor 18,000 BTU
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Cadet makes the best and nothing made in China is anyway near as good!~  and the price was OK ,  too!! Thermostat cycles as it should.", 'I bought three of these Cadet Twin-Pak heaters. They work great. Very easy to install.I would recommend these heaters to anyone that needs to add heat.']

Title: HILAND AZ Patio Heaters Bronze Patio Heater with Table 48K BTU
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: Mr. Heater Big Buddy 18,000 BTU/hr. 450 sq. ft. Radiant Propane Porta -Pack of 1
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. Title: Mr. Heater Big Buddy 18,000 BTU/hr. 450 sq. ft. Radiant Propane Porta -Pack of 1
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Title: HILAND AZ Patio Heaters Bronze Patio Heater with Table 48K BTU
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: American Wick Kerosene Heater Wick -Case of 12
Reviews: ['I got these wicks for my antique Perfection kerosene heaters (I bought several more to keep on hand after trying two). In my opinion, this wick actually out-performs the (new old stock) Perfection Brand wicks available for sale, which can be smelly from age, sometimes bent or rusted, and the cotton wick material, itself, tends to be a bit stiff from age, and occasionally are reconditioned or simply moved in the carrier to appear to be new when they are, in fact, used. I\'ve had that result twice from buying "new" old stock Perfection Brand wicks. This American Wick AW-500 fits perfectly, works smoothly, and is made with superior materials and craftsmanship. The wick is all cotton, heavy-duty and is long-lasting. It\'s clean-burning and there is no smoke or odor. The steel wick carrier is sturdy and smooth. Unlike the Perfection Brand wick, the American AW-500 is constructed with 4 splits in the lower part which go into the tank, creating 4 "tails" (NOTE: The lower portion of the wick is not visible in photo, as they are tucked inside its own cylindrical carrier in packaging, and in the photo). The American Wick AW-500 wick is very similar to the Perfection Brand 500 wick, but the Perfection  wick is split in 2 places and has 2 tails. In my opinion, the American AW-500 wick with 4 tails works better and is easier to install, because the 4-way tail split allows the wick tales to be more easily maneuvered around the wick adjuster, to seat a bit lower when turned down, and the tails to dip deeper into the kerosene tank and are more neatly adjusted up and down without binding at all. The cost of this item is very reasonable and I think it\'s a great value, compared with the usually higher-priced original Perfection 500 wicks to be found for sale. I hesitated at first to buy this non-Perfection part for my Perfection heaters, but after a couple of bad experiences with the more costly Perfection wicks, I am so glad I took the chance and bought the American AW-500 wicks! I\'m extremely pleased! I highly recommend this excellent product! ', "These are not very heavy weight, the weave is loose, and they are not even close to the high quality brand name wick I order from England.  Cosmetically it's not nice looking as an original Perfection wick . Heavy metal wick sleeve is good and they are nicely fastened with metal riveting. They will work just fine in a Perfection 500 heater they just don't last as long as the other brand I buy and they will burn down a little bit faster.  If I can get a good deal on an AW-500 wick or this is the only one available it is much better than a fiberglass wick. Just make sure that you are gentle installing the wick and if one gets a lot of tar from contaminated fuel, moisture,  improper use,  and sticky in the wick gallery these will tear. Odor wise they will smell terrible when you burn one in for the first time that is normal because they are not pre charred. If you run at the highest flame setting possible in the Perfection 500  heater burning good quality kerosene they will do a good job. I use a Perfection 500 heater burning clear kerosene every day year round as my only source of heat and for cooking? If I can get a good deal on one or more of these AW500 wicks I will buy them.   ", 'Excellent quality.  AW-45 is lower part of a mechanical wick; AW-40 is the top part only; AW-49 is both top and bottom.  AW-45, as the bottom only, appears to be no longer available from wick manufacturers.  Grab them if you can find them!', 'Fits just as it should. Burns great in my Perfection M525 Heater. Will definitely buy again, although this one will last me for a few years.', 'Much better quality wick than even more expense wicks out there.  This one burns like the OEM all cotton wick with normal  charring as it should.  Other wicks I have used seem to have a high percentage of nylon or other synthetic and leave a hard residue after just one or two burns that is then hard to relight.  This wick has none of that and I will buy buy another just to have one hand. ', "I was skeptical to purchase at first, considering they don't manufacture the Perfection Heaters anymore, but I took a chance and was very happy this wick is quite similar to an original Perfection wick, and it's 100% cotton. The only issue I experienced was that the gear holes on the wick canister didn't exactly line up correctly. Fortunately I was able to transfer the wick to the original wick canister which has gear holes all around it, making it much easier to install.", 'I had to get another one because it had burned down. When I forget to turn off the heater, the wick will burn down one quarter of an inch each time. I probably will be ordering another soon. Thanks for the product and price.', 'Heater is 100yrs. old, was easy to install,glad wick was still available.', 'These were great! I have two 50 year old vintage kerosene heater and these worked out perfectly!! I highly recommend these!', "The next best thing to the 'Perfection' brand wick. Second one I bought. Very dependable."]

Title: HILAND AZ Patio Heaters Bronze Patio Heater with Table 48K BTU
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. Title: American Wick Kerosene Heater Wick -Case of 12
Reviews: ['I got these wicks for my antique Perfection kerosene heaters (I bought several more to keep on hand after trying two). In my opinion, this wick actually out-performs the (new old stock) Perfection Brand wicks available for sale, which can be smelly from age, sometimes bent or rusted, and the cotton wick material, itself, tends to be a bit stiff from age, and occasionally are reconditioned or simply moved in the carrier to appear to be new when they are, in fact, used. I\'ve had that result twice from buying "new" old stock Perfection Brand wicks. This American Wick AW-500 fits perfectly, works smoothly, and is made with superior materials and craftsmanship. The wick is all cotton, heavy-duty and is long-lasting. It\'s clean-burning and there is no smoke or odor. The steel wick carrier is sturdy and smooth. Unlike the Perfection Brand wick, the American AW-500 is constructed with 4 splits in the lower part which go into the tank, creating 4 "tails" (NOTE: The lower portion of the wick is not visible in photo, as they are tucked inside its own cylindrical carrier in packaging, and in the photo). The American Wick AW-500 wick is very similar to the Perfection Brand 500 wick, but the Perfection  wick is split in 2 places and has 2 tails. In my opinion, the American AW-500 wick with 4 tails works better and is easier to install, because the 4-way tail split allows the wick tales to be more easily maneuvered around the wick adjuster, to seat a bit lower when turned down, and the tails to dip deeper into the kerosene tank and are more neatly adjusted up and down without binding at all. The cost of this item is very reasonable and I think it\'s a great value, compared with the usually higher-priced original Perfection 500 wicks to be found for sale. I hesitated at first to buy this non-Perfection part for my Perfection heaters, but after a couple of bad experiences with the more costly Perfection wicks, I am so glad I took the chance and bought the American AW-500 wicks! I\'m extremely pleased! I highly recommend this excellent product! ', "These are not very heavy weight, the weave is loose, and they are not even close to the high quality brand name wick I order from England.  Cosmetically it's not nice looking as an original Perfection wick . Heavy metal wick sleeve is good and they are nicely fastened with metal riveting. They will work just fine in a Perfection 500 heater they just don't last as long as the other brand I buy and they will burn down a little bit faster.  If I can get a good deal on an AW-500 wick or this is the only one available it is much better than a fiberglass wick. Just make sure that you are gentle installing the wick and if one gets a lot of tar from contaminated fuel, moisture,  improper use,  and sticky in the wick gallery these will tear. Odor wise they will smell terrible when you burn one in for the first time that is normal because they are not pre charred. If you run at the highest flame setting possible in the Perfection 500  heater burning good quality kerosene they will do a good job. I use a Perfection 500 heater burning clear kerosene every day year round as my only source of heat and for cooking? If I can get a good deal on one or more of these AW500 wicks I will buy them.   ", 'Excellent quality.  AW-45 is lower part of a mechanical wick; AW-40 is the top part only; AW-49 is both top and bottom.  AW-45, as the bottom only, appears to be no longer available from wick manufacturers.  Grab them if you can find them!', 'Fits just as it should. Burns great in my Perfection M525 Heater. Will definitely buy again, although this one will last me for a few years.', 'Much better quality wick than even more expense wicks out there.  This one burns like the OEM all cotton wick with normal  charring as it should.  Other wicks I have used seem to have a high percentage of nylon or other synthetic and leave a hard residue after just one or two burns that is then hard to relight.  This wick has none of that and I will buy buy another just to have one hand. ', "I was skeptical to purchase at first, considering they don't manufacture the Perfection Heaters anymore, but I took a chance and was very happy this wick is quite similar to an original Perfection wick, and it's 100% cotton. The only issue I experienced was that the gear holes on the wick canister didn't exactly line up correctly. Fortunately I was able to transfer the wick to the original wick canister which has gear holes all around it, making it much easier to install.", 'I had to get another one because it had burned down. When I forget to turn off the heater, the wick will burn down one quarter of an inch each time. I probably will be ordering another soon. Thanks for the product and price.', 'Heater is 100yrs. old, was easy to install,glad wick was still available.', 'These were great! I have two 50 year old vintage kerosene heater and these worked out perfectly!! I highly recommend these!', "The next best thing to the 'Perfection' brand wick. Second one I bought. Very dependable."]

Title: HILAND AZ Patio Heaters Bronze Patio Heater with Table 48K BTU
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! Title: American Wick Kerosene Heater Wick -Case of 12
Reviews: ['I got these wicks for my antique Perfection kerosene heaters (I bought several more to keep on hand after trying two). In my opinion, this wick actually out-performs the (new old stock) Perfection Brand wicks available for sale, which can be smelly from age, sometimes bent or rusted, and the cotton wick material, itself, tends to be a bit stiff from age, and occasionally are reconditioned or simply moved in the carrier to appear to be new when they are, in fact, used. I\'ve had that result twice from buying "new" old stock Perfection Brand wicks. This American Wick AW-500 fits perfectly, works smoothly, and is made with superior materials and craftsmanship. The wick is all cotton, heavy-duty and is long-lasting. It\'s clean-burning and there is no smoke or odor. The steel wick carrier is sturdy and smooth. Unlike the Perfection Brand wick, the American AW-500 is constructed with 4 splits in the lower part which go into the tank, creating 4 "tails" (NOTE: The lower portion of the wick is not visible in photo, as they are tucked inside its own cylindrical carrier in packaging, and in the photo). The American Wick AW-500 wick is very similar to the Perfection Brand 500 wick, but the Perfection  wick is split in 2 places and has 2 tails. In my opinion, the American AW-500 wick with 4 tails works better and is easier to install, because the 4-way tail split allows the wick tales to be more easily maneuvered around the wick adjuster, to seat a bit lower when turned down, and the tails to dip deeper into the kerosene tank and are more neatly adjusted up and down without binding at all. The cost of this item is very reasonable and I think it\'s a great value, compared with the usually higher-priced original Perfection 500 wicks to be found for sale. I hesitated at first to buy this non-Perfection part for my Perfection heaters, but after a couple of bad experiences with the more costly Perfection wicks, I am so glad I took the chance and bought the American AW-500 wicks! I\'m extremely pleased! I highly recommend this excellent product! ', "These are not very heavy weight, the weave is loose, and they are not even close to the high quality brand name wick I order from England.  Cosmetically it's not nice looking as an original Perfection wick . Heavy metal wick sleeve is good and they are nicely fastened with metal riveting. They will work just fine in a Perfection 500 heater they just don't last as long as the other brand I buy and they will burn down a little bit faster.  If I can get a good deal on an AW-500 wick or this is the only one available it is much better than a fiberglass wick. Just make sure that you are gentle installing the wick and if one gets a lot of tar from contaminated fuel, moisture,  improper use,  and sticky in the wick gallery these will tear. Odor wise they will smell terrible when you burn one in for the first time that is normal because they are not pre charred. If you run at the highest flame setting possible in the Perfection 500  heater burning good quality kerosene they will do a good job. I use a Perfection 500 heater burning clear kerosene every day year round as my only source of heat and for cooking? If I can get a good deal on one or more of these AW500 wicks I will buy them.   ", 'Excellent quality.  AW-45 is lower part of a mechanical wick; AW-40 is the top part only; AW-49 is both top and bottom.  AW-45, as the bottom only, appears to be no longer available from wick manufacturers.  Grab them if you can find them!', 'Fits just as it should. Burns great in my Perfection M525 Heater. Will definitely buy again, although this one will last me for a few years.', 'Much better quality wick than even more expense wicks out there.  This one burns like the OEM all cotton wick with normal  charring as it should.  Other wicks I have used seem to have a high percentage of nylon or other synthetic and leave a hard residue after just one or two burns that is then hard to relight.  This wick has none of that and I will buy buy another just to have one hand. ', "I was skeptical to purchase at first, considering they don't manufacture the Perfection Heaters anymore, but I took a chance and was very happy this wick is quite similar to an original Perfection wick, and it's 100% cotton. The only issue I experienced was that the gear holes on the wick canister didn't exactly line up correctly. Fortunately I was able to transfer the wick to the original wick canister which has gear holes all around it, making it much easier to install.", 'I had to get another one because it had burned down. When I forget to turn off the heater, the wick will burn down one quarter of an inch each time. I probably will be ordering another soon. Thanks for the product and price.', 'Heater is 100yrs. old, was easy to install,glad wick was still available.', 'These were great! I have two 50 year old vintage kerosene heater and these worked out perfectly!! I highly recommend these!', "The next best thing to the 'Perfection' brand wick. Second one I bought. Very dependable."]

Title: Mr Heater Blue Flame 20000 Btu Natural Gas Vent Free Heater
Reviews: ['Our Mr. Heater natural gas heater warms our enclosed deck area quickly.  We leave the pilot light on when we\'re not using the "porch".  The area warms up quickly on #2 setting and we turn the overhead fan on low.  It\'s a much better and faster heat than the small electric heater we\'ve used the past couple years.  Also, it\'s been very cold the past week with highs in the teens and we\'ve been very comfortable.  Love this heater!', 'I wall mount this heater. It consistently works, and heats great! Make sure you leave a window open slightly when using this heater. I highly recommend it!', 'installed in garage approx. 600 sq. ft.  works good, because of garage ceiling is high 12ft.  had to install ceiling fan together works very good', 'SHIPPING WAS AHEAD OF DAY PROMISED. ONLY TOOK 20 MIN. TO HOOK IT UP.HEATER WORK GREAT AND IT HAS VERIBLE HEATER ADJUSTMENTS SO YOU CAN TURN IT WAY DOWN TO SAVE GAS.', "All is good except it doesn't turn on or off properly,  it sputters between cycles, like if the diaphragm isn't closing all the way, bought a blower for it , now thats a waste of money. I was expecting a cold winter and put on the gas line for this heater, instead of electric like last year, so far it hit the low 20's in texas only a time or two, hangs round 30 for overnight lows, never got the dial above 3 and been comfortable, it just sputters", 'Very clean,no gas smell, and it works flawlessly...well done', 'Lit on the first click of the igniter and has been burning ever since.', 'I installed the heater this weekend it was a easy install an works great', 'small and powerful although it does put off a slight odor.', 'Looks good.']

Title: HILAND AZ Patio Heaters Bronze Patio Heater with Table 48K BTU
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: American Wick Kerosene Heater Wick -Case of 12
Reviews: ['I got these wicks for my antique Perfection kerosene heaters (I bought several more to keep on hand after trying two). In my opinion, this wick actually out-performs the (new old stock) Perfection Brand wicks available for sale, which can be smelly from age, sometimes bent or rusted, and the cotton wick material, itself, tends to be a bit stiff from age, and occasionally are reconditioned or simply moved in the carrier to appear to be new when they are, in fact, used. I\'ve had that result twice from buying "new" old stock Perfection Brand wicks. This American Wick AW-500 fits perfectly, works smoothly, and is made with superior materials and craftsmanship. The wick is all cotton, heavy-duty and is long-lasting. It\'s clean-burning and there is no smoke or odor. The steel wick carrier is sturdy and smooth. Unlike the Perfection Brand wick, the American AW-500 is constructed with 4 splits in the lower part which go into the tank, creating 4 "tails" (NOTE: The lower portion of the wick is not visible in photo, as they are tucked inside its own cylindrical carrier in packaging, and in the photo). The American Wick AW-500 wick is very similar to the Perfection Brand 500 wick, but the Perfection  wick is split in 2 places and has 2 tails. In my opinion, the American AW-500 wick with 4 tails works better and is easier to install, because the 4-way tail split allows the wick tales to be more easily maneuvered around the wick adjuster, to seat a bit lower when turned down, and the tails to dip deeper into the kerosene tank and are more neatly adjusted up and down without binding at all. The cost of this item is very reasonable and I think it\'s a great value, compared with the usually higher-priced original Perfection 500 wicks to be found for sale. I hesitated at first to buy this non-Perfection part for my Perfection heaters, but after a couple of bad experiences with the more costly Perfection wicks, I am so glad I took the chance and bought the American AW-500 wicks! I\'m extremely pleased! I highly recommend this excellent product! ', "These are not very heavy weight, the weave is loose, and they are not even close to the high quality brand name wick I order from England.  Cosmetically it's not nice looking as an original Perfection wick . Heavy metal wick sleeve is good and they are nicely fastened with metal riveting. They will work just fine in a Perfection 500 heater they just don't last as long as the other brand I buy and they will burn down a little bit faster.  If I can get a good deal on an AW-500 wick or this is the only one available it is much better than a fiberglass wick. Just make sure that you are gentle installing the wick and if one gets a lot of tar from contaminated fuel, moisture,  improper use,  and sticky in the wick gallery these will tear. Odor wise they will smell terrible when you burn one in for the first time that is normal because they are not pre charred. If you run at the highest flame setting possible in the Perfection 500  heater burning good quality kerosene they will do a good job. I use a Perfection 500 heater burning clear kerosene every day year round as my only source of heat and for cooking? If I can get a good deal on one or more of these AW500 wicks I will buy them.   ", 'Excellent quality.  AW-45 is lower part of a mechanical wick; AW-40 is the top part only; AW-49 is both top and bottom.  AW-45, as the bottom only, appears to be no longer available from wick manufacturers.  Grab them if you can find them!', 'Fits just as it should. Burns great in my Perfection M525 Heater. Will definitely buy again, although this one will last me for a few years.', 'Much better quality wick than even more expense wicks out there.  This one burns like the OEM all cotton wick with normal  charring as it should.  Other wicks I have used seem to have a high percentage of nylon or other synthetic and leave a hard residue after just one or two burns that is then hard to relight.  This wick has none of that and I will buy buy another just to have one hand. ', "I was skeptical to purchase at first, considering they don't manufacture the Perfection Heaters anymore, but I took a chance and was very happy this wick is quite similar to an original Perfection wick, and it's 100% cotton. The only issue I experienced was that the gear holes on the wick canister didn't exactly line up correctly. Fortunately I was able to transfer the wick to the original wick canister which has gear holes all around it, making it much easier to install.", 'I had to get another one because it had burned down. When I forget to turn off the heater, the wick will burn down one quarter of an inch each time. I probably will be ordering another soon. Thanks for the product and price.', 'Heater is 100yrs. old, was easy to install,glad wick was still available.', 'These were great! I have two 50 year old vintage kerosene heater and these worked out perfectly!! I highly recommend these!', "The next best thing to the 'Perfection' brand wick. Second one I bought. Very dependable."]
