Title: LifeSmart 1500 W Portable Electric Infrared Quartz Fireplace Heater, Indoor Use
Reviews: ["We're overall happy with this heater but you need to have realistic expectations. Heating 1,800 sq feet? That's beyond optomistic, it's absurd. We set it up in our 25x15 living room and it can warm up that area if you leave it on for half the day. I probably would have been upset if I paid full retail and expected it to heat the entire 2,000 sq ft home. With that said, I paid roughly $120 for this unit refurbished (looks and acts good as new) and still thinks it's well worth it. Quality: It's well built and a solid piece of furniture.Looks: The wood looks great and the flames are really nice. It defintely adds to the room.", "I bought this heater thinking it would produce enough heat to atleast heat my living room which isn't to big but nope still cold it does look cool while it's on I will say that and also when I bought it, it arrived damaged now the company did offer me a partial refund which I got back part of my money but only because I've been through these situations before where you send an item back everyone drags their feet you wait forever to fix the initial problem so I just said ok and went with it but my honest opinion I would not buy another one not really worth it in my opinion.", 'I have been heating with a corn heater.  I really like the corn heater, but I am on o2 now and at times you have to open the door on the corn heater and you have an open flame. Open flame and o2  does nit work well with each other.  I do have a 24000  ac with 18000   heat pump.  that I do turn on if it is real cold just to take the chill out of the room.   I an using the LS-1111HH13 infrared fireplace in a room about 20x35  around 700 sq. feet. and it keeps the room toasty.         Ray Phillips', "I absolutely love this. I don't need the heater much here in Florida, but tried it once and it worked perfectly...very warm on my back porch. I use the fireplace setting every day and night. It is beautiful and realistic. There are cheaper ones out there, but research first. This one is fully assembled. Pull it out of the box and plug it in. It is real wood and on casters for easy movement. I want one for my living room as a tv stand but I don't have the money right now. Maybe next year. AAA brand.", "Pros  price. Heat output is as expected.Lots of people complain it won't heat the 1800 sq ft home.Did you read the listing?Sets a mood without the mess of fire wood.Good for smaller rooms and such.", "The description says this will heat up to 1800 sq ft. I didn't really expect to do that to be honest. 1800 sq. ft is a fairly large house. But this won't heat my small living room !. Bought it cheap so I guess I got what I paid for it. Would not recommend buying one except for maybe a SMALL bedroom.", "Love, Love, Love it!  I have an old farmhouse that I use a fireplace to heat, this heater pulls heat from one end of my home to the other to keep an even temperature throughout.  I didn't think it was possible to not have to use space heaters but this one has taken the place of 4.  The cabinet it beautiful and the dogs have a second favorite place to sleep now, (the first is with me).", "I bought the fireplace/heater for  my daughter for Christmas. They loved it right off. Then they plugged it in and were more amazed by the way it heated their living room. Though it has not been very cold here,yet, they expect it to be a big help on their heating bill this year, They  also like the ambiance and glow it gives the room.  I don't believe I could have gotten them anything that would have suited them more for the price.", 'Received the Fireplace heats my room very well. I like the remote very easy to use. I would recommend this to my family and friends.', 'I love it! It looks good and heat a small area just fine. Using it keeps my electric bill low. I highly recommend any infrared heater.']

Title: AZ Patio Heaters 41,000 BTU Hammered Bronze Gas Patio Heater - HLDS01-CGT
Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: - EdenPURE GEN3 1000 Quartz Infrared Portable Space Heater -nolonger in box
Reviews: ["No instructions so take pics of old one with wires attatched. Then hook up new one, need to bend an optical sensor middle of board before installing new board into front cover so Just bend like the old one, also make note of LEDs because they need to fit into their individual positions. Just bend like old ones as well. Before you re-install front panel back-on heater housing and have the board installed in the front panel, make sure all the font cover push buttons click on and release, in other words return to position once you have actuated them. My board had a slight bend in it and would not allow one of the push switches to actuate as it was jammed into actuated position and would not release due to the bend in the PCB of the board. I simply backed off two of the mounting screws allowing the PCB to float just a bit allowing the buttons to actuate and release like they should. Not a big deal in leaving the PCB a little loose as it will not be going anywhere once you complete the installation.At first I was a little disappointed with the cycling action of the heater once it was installed. But what I did not take into account was that the heater needed to cycle to sense the correct room temp for the new board and after 4-6hrsit was back working great. Don't be surprised if you show a different number of LEDs lit with the new board compared to your old one due to temp sensing differences from one board to the next.Overall I like these heaters. They work great to Supplement your houses main heat source. I have mine against an inside wall pointed toward my main entrance to the house. After owning it for about five years I know for a fact it is saving me $30-$40 per month depending on the price of home heating oil. When oil was 4.65per gal, I was saving well over $50-$60 a month. I live in Alaska for what its worth and it runs/cycles 12months out of every year, and might get turned totally off for a total of 2weeks out of those 12months.", "EdenPure's first heater endorsed by Bob Villa.  They no longer make this model which is over ten years old.  This model is reliable and energy efficient and safe in the home.  It has rollers and can be moved from room to room is necessary.  Heat is constant and comfortable.", 'Really like these heaters as this is my 2nd one. Very safe around pets and kids as there are no hot surfaces and it is whisper quiet. The remote control is very handy also.', 'Very fast shipment part was dead on easy to install and works great thanks. A+++', 'Works very well ', 'All I can say is that I love it!', 'Love this small heater box , can be transported anywhere ', 'This product was a gift to a disabled family member.  Its performance and ease of use demonstrate that this was a good buy as well as a wise choice.  I heartily recommend this heater. ', 'easy to install, saved me $200.00', 'Would be better if it had a thermostat ']

Title: Mr. Heater MH18B Propane Heater Red
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Title: DAYTON Portable Electric Jobsite  3VU36
Reviews: ["I'm currently on my 3rd Dayton  heater, all the same model, over two winters. Iuse it for heating an attached greenhouse with double pane glass, dimensions14 x 25' and a story and a half tall.  I live in Duluth, MN with temps thatcan easily get down to -20 to -30.  All that being said, the heater does a goodjob keeping the greenhouse at 60 degrees with temps -20.  The first one lastedonly weeks before a short circuiting (?) problem, and I exchanged for a new oneunder the one year warrenty.  The second one only lasted a few days on it's second winter when the heating element no longer functioned, though the fan still did run.  I exchanged that one under a Square Trade warrenty and so farit has worked well.  Keep in mind the heater runs on 220 volts, so depending onwhat you pay for electricity your monthly costs can add up.  I would alsorecommend keeping it out of very humid conditions, and I always remove it fromthe greenhouse when watering and for several hours after until the greenhousehas dried out a bit.  I think it would work very well for a garage or detachedbuilding.  Just don't know if it is as rugged as I would want, but perhaps things are built nowdays as being more disposable.  Regardless, I would make sure you have a warrenty to protect yourself.", 'I bought this little heater to heat my 24 x 24 semi-insulated workshop. The walls are insulated, but the ceiling is just 1/2 inch plywood with no insulation. When I first unpacked the Dayton 3VU36, I was skeptical because of its size. Boy was I fooled.First run - Garage temp was 34 degrees (23 degrees outside with ice on the ground). Within 15 minutes, there was an increase of 14 degrees in the shop area. At 30 minutes, there was an increase of 22 degrees total (shop temp 56 degrees).The noise level is no different that the little box fan that I run in the summer. Not bad at all.Overall, I am a little shocked as to how well it is actually working. I would definately recommend it to a friend or family member. However..... I think it might struggle a little if used in an uninsulated area.', 'Used more to dry the moisture out of the air after warming with a torpedo propane heater in my shop.  Good to use for small area as main heat. Quiet for a 220 heater.', 'If you are serious about heating, and I mean really heating, your garage or shop, then a 240 volt heater is the way to go.  The 110 volt cheap heaters only produce about 1500 watts on maximum.  This 240 volt heater produces 5600 watts.  You do the math! It is necessary to wire a 240 volt outlet into your system but worth the trouble.', 'love the Heater', 'works well for the price, we use it to keep a greenhouse above 60 degrees in the winter months with outside temps at or around 8 degrees. This does a good job and worth the $99 investment.', 'Good unit as a temporary (part time) heater. Used to heat a two stall garage space while working on a car.Does require an electricial to run a 220 service to plug in the heater.A little noisy but does throw heat.', "I'm going into my fourth heater in 4 years. They only last a year or less and it's impossible to get parts. When they work, they're great. They just don't last."]

Reviews: ["We're overall happy with this heater but you need to have realistic expectations. Heating 1,800 sq feet? That's beyond optomistic, it's absurd. I probably would have been upset if I paid full retail and expected it to heat the entire 2,000 sq ft home. With that said, I paid roughly $120 for this unit refurbished (looks and acts good as new) and still thinks it's well worth it. Quality: It's well built and a solid piece of furniture.Looks: The wood looks great and the flames are really nice. It defintely adds to the room.", "I bought this heater thinking it would produce enough heat to atleast heat my living room which isn't to big but nope still cold it does look cool while it's on I will say that and also when I bought it, it arrived damaged now the company did offer me a partial refund which I got back part of my money but only because I've been through these situations before where you send an item back everyone drags their feet you wait forever to fix the initial problem so I just said ok and went with it but my honest opinion I would not buy another one not really worth it in my opinion.", 'I have been heating with a corn heater.  I really like the corn heater, but I am on o2 now and at times you have to open the door on the corn heater and you have an open flame. Open flame and o2  does nit work well with each other.  I do have a 24000  ac with 18000   heat pump.  that I do turn on if it is real cold just to take the chill out of the room. Title: - EdenPURE GEN3 1000 Quartz Infrared Portable Space Heater -nolonger in box
Reviews: ["No instructions so take pics of old one with wires attatched. Then hook up new one, need to bend an optical sensor middle of board before installing new board into front cover so Just bend like the old one, also make note of LEDs because they need to fit into their individual positions. Just bend like old ones as well. Before you re-install front panel back-on heater housing and have the board installed in the front panel, make sure all the font cover push buttons click on and release, in other words return to position once you have actuated them. My board had a slight bend in it and would not allow one of the push switches to actuate as it was jammed into actuated position and would not release due to the bend in the PCB of the board. I simply backed off two of the mounting screws allowing the PCB to float just a bit allowing the buttons to actuate and release like they should. Not a big deal in leaving the PCB a little loose as it will not be going anywhere once you complete the installation.At first I was a little disappointed with the cycling action of the heater once it was installed. But what I did not take into account was that the heater needed to cycle to sense the correct room temp for the new board and after 4-6hrsit was back working great. Don't be surprised if you show a different number of LEDs lit with the new board compared to your old one due to temp sensing differences from one board to the next.Overall I like these heaters. They work great to Supplement your houses main heat source. I have mine against an inside wall pointed toward my main entrance to the house. After owning it for about five years I know for a fact it is saving me $30-$40 per month depending on the price of home heating oil. When oil was 4.65per gal, I was saving well over $50-$60 a month. I live in Alaska for what its worth and it runs/cycles 12months out of every year, and might get turned totally off for a total of 2weeks out of those 12months.", "EdenPure's first heater endorsed by Bob Villa.  They no longer make this model which is over ten years old.  This model is reliable and energy efficient and safe in the home.  It has rollers and can be moved from room to room is necessary.  Heat is constant and comfortable.", 'Really like these heaters as this is my 2nd one. Very safe around pets and kids as there are no hot surfaces and it is whisper quiet. The remote control is very handy also.', 'Very fast shipment part was dead on easy to install and works great thanks. A+++', 'Works very well ', 'All I can say is that I love it!', 'Love this small heater box , can be transported anywhere ', 'This product was a gift to a disabled family member.  Its performance and ease of use demonstrate that this was a good buy as well as a wise choice.  I heartily recommend this heater. ', 'easy to install, saved me $200.00', 'Would be better if it had a thermostat ']

Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Title: DAYTON Portable Electric Jobsite  3VU36
Reviews: ["I'm currently on my 3rd Dayton  heater, all the same model, over two winters. Iuse it for heating an attached greenhouse with double pane glass, dimensions14 x 25' and a story and a half tall.  I live in Duluth, MN with temps thatcan easily get down to -20 to -30.  All that being said, the heater does a goodjob keeping the greenhouse at 60 degrees with temps -20.  The first one lastedonly weeks before a short circuiting (?) problem, and I exchanged for a new oneunder the one year warrenty.  The second one only lasted a few days on it's second winter when the heating element no longer functioned, though the fan still did run.  I exchanged that one under a Square Trade warrenty and so farit has worked well.  Keep in mind the heater runs on 220 volts, so depending onwhat you pay for electricity your monthly costs can add up.  I would alsorecommend keeping it out of very humid conditions, and I always remove it fromthe greenhouse when watering and for several hours after until the greenhousehas dried out a bit.  I think it would work very well for a garage or detachedbuilding.  Just don't know if it is as rugged as I would want, but perhaps things are built nowdays as being more disposable.  Regardless, I would make sure you have a warrenty to protect yourself.", 'I bought this little heater to heat my 24 x 24 semi-insulated workshop. The walls are insulated, but the ceiling is just 1/2 inch plywood with no insulation. When I first unpacked the Dayton 3VU36, I was skeptical because of its size. Boy was I fooled.First run - Garage temp was 34 degrees (23 degrees outside with ice on the ground). Within 15 minutes, there was an increase of 14 degrees in the shop area. At 30 minutes, there was an increase of 22 degrees total (shop temp 56 degrees).The noise level is no different that the little box fan that I run in the summer. Not bad at all.Overall, I am a little shocked as to how well it is actually working. I would definately recommend it to a friend or family member. However..... I think it might struggle a little if used in an uninsulated area.', 'Used more to dry the moisture out of the air after warming with a torpedo propane heater in my shop.  Good to use for small area as main heat. Quiet for a 220 heater.', 'If you are serious about heating, and I mean really heating, your garage or shop, then a 240 volt heater is the way to go.  The 110 volt cheap heaters only produce about 1500 watts on maximum.  This 240 volt heater produces 5600 watts.  You do the math! It is necessary to wire a 240 volt outlet into your system but worth the trouble.', 'love the Heater', 'works well for the price, we use it to keep a greenhouse above 60 degrees in the winter months with outside temps at or around 8 degrees. This does a good job and worth the $99 investment.', 'Good unit as a temporary (part time) heater. Used to heat a two stall garage space while working on a car.Does require an electricial to run a 220 service to plug in the heater.A little noisy but does throw heat.', "I'm going into my fourth heater in 4 years. They only last a year or less and it's impossible to get parts. When they work, they're great. They just don't last."]

Title: LifeSmart 1500 W Portable Electric Infrared Quartz Fireplace Heater, Indoor Use
Reviews: ["We're overall happy with this heater but you need to have realistic expectations. Heating 1,800 sq feet? That's beyond optomistic, it's absurd. We set it up in our 25x15 living room and it can warm up that area if you leave it on for half the day. I probably would have been upset if I paid full retail and expected it to heat the entire 2,000 sq ft home. With that said, I paid roughly $120 for this unit refurbished (looks and acts good as new) and still thinks it's well worth it. Quality: It's well built and a solid piece of furniture.Looks: The wood looks great and the flames are really nice. It defintely adds to the room.", "I bought this heater thinking it would produce enough heat to atleast heat my living room which isn't to big but nope still cold it does look cool while it's on I will say that and also when I bought it, it arrived damaged now the company did offer me a partial refund which I got back part of my money but only because I've been through these situations before where you send an item back everyone drags their feet you wait forever to fix the initial problem so I just said ok and went with it but my honest opinion I would not buy another one not really worth it in my opinion.", 'I have been heating with a corn heater.  I really like the corn heater, but I am on o2 now and at times you have to open the door on the corn heater and you have an open flame. Open flame and o2  does nit work well with each other.  I do have a 24000  ac with 18000   heat pump.  that I do turn on if it is real cold just to take the chill out of the room.   I an using the LS-1111HH13 infrared fireplace in a room about 20x35  around 700 sq. feet. and it keeps the room toasty.         Ray Phillips', "I absolutely love this. I don't need the heater much here in Florida, but tried it once and it worked perfectly...very warm on my back porch. I use the fireplace setting every day and night. It is beautiful and realistic. There are cheaper ones out there, but research first. This one is fully assembled. Pull it out of the box and plug it in. It is real wood and on casters for easy movement. I want one for my living room as a tv stand but I don't have the money right now. Maybe next year. AAA brand.", "Pros  price. Heat output is as expected.Lots of people complain it won't heat the 1800 sq ft home.Did you read the listing?Sets a mood without the mess of fire wood.Good for smaller rooms and such.", "The description says this will heat up to 1800 sq ft. I didn't really expect to do that to be honest. 1800 sq. ft is a fairly large house. But this won't heat my small living room !. Bought it cheap so I guess I got what I paid for it. Would not recommend buying one except for maybe a SMALL bedroom.", "Love, Love, Love it!  I have an old farmhouse that I use a fireplace to heat, this heater pulls heat from one end of my home to the other to keep an even temperature throughout.  I didn't think it was possible to not have to use space heaters but this one has taken the place of 4.  The cabinet it beautiful and the dogs have a second favorite place to sleep now, (the first is with me).", "I bought the fireplace/heater for  my daughter for Christmas. They loved it right off. Then they plugged it in and were more amazed by the way it heated their living room. Though it has not been very cold here,yet, they expect it to be a big help on their heating bill this year, They  also like the ambiance and glow it gives the room.  I don't believe I could have gotten them anything that would have suited them more for the price.", 'Received the Fireplace heats my room very well. I like the remote very easy to use. I would recommend this to my family and friends.', 'I love it! It looks good and heat a small area just fine. Using it keeps my electric bill low. I highly recommend any infrared heater.']

Reviews: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won’t light. Very disappointing! I’m going to see if I can get it serviced since I’m desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can’t get it to light, I’m returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn’t come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

Title: - EdenPURE GEN3 1000 Quartz Infrared Portable Space Heater -nolonger in box
Reviews: ["No instructions so take pics of old one with wires attatched. Then hook up new one, need to bend an optical sensor middle of board before installing new board into front cover so Just bend like the old one, also make note of LEDs because they need to fit into their individual positions. Just bend like old ones as well. Before you re-install front panel back-on heater housing and have the board installed in the front panel, make sure all the font cover push buttons click on and release, in other words return to position once you have actuated them. My board had a slight bend in it and would not allow one of the push switches to actuate as it was jammed into actuated position and would not release due to the bend in the PCB of the board. I simply backed off two of the mounting screws allowing the PCB to float just a bit allowing the buttons to actuate and release like they should. Not a big deal in leaving the PCB a little loose as it will not be going anywhere once you complete the installation.At first I was a little disappointed with the cycling action of the heater once it was installed. But what I did not take into account was that the heater needed to cycle to sense the correct room temp for the new board and after 4-6hrsit was back working great. Don't be surprised if you show a different number of LEDs lit with the new board compared to your old one due to temp sensing differences from one board to the next.Overall I like these heaters. They work great to Supplement your houses main heat source. I have mine against an inside wall pointed toward my main entrance to the house. After owning it for about five years I know for a fact it is saving me $30-$40 per month depending on the price of home heating oil. When oil was 4.65per gal, I was saving well over $50-$60 a month. I live in Alaska for what its worth and it runs/cycles 12months out of every year, and might get turned totally off for a total of 2weeks out of those 12months.", "EdenPure's first heater endorsed by Bob Villa.  They no longer make this model which is over ten years old.  This model is reliable and energy efficient and safe in the home.  It has rollers and can be moved from room to room is necessary.  Heat is constant and comfortable.", 'Really like these heaters as this is my 2nd one. Very safe around pets and kids as there are no hot surfaces and it is whisper quiet. The remote control is very handy also.', 'Very fast shipment part was dead on easy to install and works great thanks. A+++', 'Works very well ', 'All I can say is that I love it!', 'Love this small heater box , can be transported anywhere ', 'This product was a gift to a disabled family member.  Its performance and ease of use demonstrate that this was a good buy as well as a wise choice.  I heartily recommend this heater. ', 'easy to install, saved me $200.00', 'Would be better if it had a thermostat ']

Title: Mr. Heater MH18B Propane Heater Red
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

Title: DAYTON Portable Electric Jobsite  3VU36
Reviews: ["I'm currently on my 3rd Dayton  heater, all the same model, over two winters. Iuse it for heating an attached greenhouse with double pane glass, dimensions14 x 25' and a story and a half tall.  I live in Duluth, MN with temps thatcan easily get down to -20 to -30.  All that being said, the heater does a goodjob keeping the greenhouse at 60 degrees with temps -20.  The first one lastedonly weeks before a short circuiting (?) problem, and I exchanged for a new oneunder the one year warrenty.  The second one only lasted a few days on it's second winter when the heating element no longer functioned, though the fan still did run.  I exchanged that one under a Square Trade warrenty and so farit has worked well.  Keep in mind the heater runs on 220 volts, so depending onwhat you pay for electricity your monthly costs can add up.  I would alsorecommend keeping it out of very humid conditions, and I always remove it fromthe greenhouse when watering and for several hours after until the greenhousehas dried out a bit.  I think it would work very well for a garage or detachedbuilding.  Just don't know if it is as rugged as I would want, but perhaps things are built nowdays as being more disposable.  Regardless, I would make sure you have a warrenty to protect yourself.", 'I bought this little heater to heat my 24 x 24 semi-insulated workshop. The walls are insulated, but the ceiling is just 1/2 inch plywood with no insulation. When I first unpacked the Dayton 3VU36, I was skeptical because of its size. Boy was I fooled.First run - Garage temp was 34 degrees (23 degrees outside with ice on the ground). Within 15 minutes, there was an increase of 14 degrees in the shop area. At 30 minutes, there was an increase of 22 degrees total (shop temp 56 degrees).The noise level is no different that the little box fan that I run in the summer. Not bad at all.Overall, I am a little shocked as to how well it is actually working. I would definately recommend it to a friend or family member. However..... I think it might struggle a little if used in an uninsulated area.', 'Used more to dry the moisture out of the air after warming with a torpedo propane heater in my shop.  Good to use for small area as main heat. Quiet for a 220 heater.', 'If you are serious about heating, and I mean really heating, your garage or shop, then a 240 volt heater is the way to go.  The 110 volt cheap heaters only produce about 1500 watts on maximum.  This 240 volt heater produces 5600 watts.  You do the math! It is necessary to wire a 240 volt outlet into your system but worth the trouble.', 'love the Heater', 'works well for the price, we use it to keep a greenhouse above 60 degrees in the winter months with outside temps at or around 8 degrees. This does a good job and worth the $99 investment.', 'Good unit as a temporary (part time) heater. Used to heat a two stall garage space while working on a car.Does require an electricial to run a 220 service to plug in the heater.A little noisy but does throw heat.', "I'm going into my fourth heater in 4 years. They only last a year or less and it's impossible to get parts. When they work, they're great. They just don't last."]

Reviews: ["We're overall happy with this heater but you need to have realistic expectations. Heating 1,800 sq feet? That's beyond optomistic, it's absurd. We set it up in our 25x15 living room and it can warm up that area if you leave it on for half the day. I probably would have been upset if I paid full retail and expected it to heat the entire 2,000 sq ft home. With that said, I paid roughly $120 for this unit refurbished (looks and acts good as new) and still thinks it's well worth it. Quality: It's well built and a solid piece of furniture.Looks: The wood looks great and the flames are really nice. It defintely adds to the room.", "I bought this heater thinking it would produce enough heat to atleast heat my living room which isn't to big but nope still cold it does look cool while it's on I will say that and also when I bought it, it arrived damaged now the company did offer me a partial refund which I got back part of my money but only because I've been through these situations before where you send an item back everyone drags their feet you wait forever to fix the initial problem so I just said ok and went with it but my honest opinion I would not buy another one not really worth it in my opinion.", 'I have been heating with a corn heater.  I really like the corn heater, but I am on o2 now and at times you have to open the door on the corn heater and you have an open flame. Open flame and o2  does nit work well with each other.  I do have a 24000  ac with 18000   heat pump.  that I do turn on if it is real cold just to take the chill out of the room.   I an using the LS-1111HH13 infrared fireplace in a room about 20x35  around 700 sq. feet. and it keeps the room toasty.         Ray Phillips', "I absolutely love this. I don't need the heater much here in Florida, but tried it once and it worked perfectly...very warm on my back porch. I use the fireplace setting every day and night. It is beautiful and realistic. There are cheaper ones out there, but research first. This one is fully assembled. Pull it out of the box and plug it in. It is real wood and on casters for easy movement. I want one for my living room as a tv stand but I don't have the money right now. Maybe next year. AAA brand.", "Pros  price. Heat output is as expected.Lots of people complain it won't heat the 1800 sq ft home.Did you read the listing?Sets a mood without the mess of fire wood.Good for smaller rooms and such.", "The description says this will heat up to 1800 sq ft. I didn't really expect to do that to be honest. 1800 sq. ft is a fairly large house. But this won't heat my small living room !. Bought it cheap so I guess I got what I paid for it. Would not recommend buying one except for maybe a SMALL bedroom.", "Love, Love, Love it!  I have an old farmhouse that I use a fireplace to heat, this heater pulls heat from one end of my home to the other to keep an even temperature throughout.  I didn't think it was possible to not have to use space heaters but this one has taken the place of 4.  The cabinet it beautiful and the dogs have a second favorite place to sleep now, (the first is with me).", "I bought the fireplace/heater for  my daughter for Christmas. They loved it right off. Then they plugged it in and were more amazed by the way it heated their living room. Though it has not been very cold here,yet, they expect it to be a big help on their heating bill this year, They  also like the ambiance and glow it gives the room.  I don't believe I could have gotten them anything that would have suited them more for the price.", 'Received the Fireplace heats my room very well. I like the remote very easy to use. I would recommend this to my family and friends.', 'I love it! It looks good and heat a small area just fine. Using it keeps my electric bill low. I highly recommend any infrared heater.']

Title: - EdenPURE GEN3 1000 Quartz Infrared Portable Space Heater -nolonger in box
Reviews: ["No instructions so take pics of old one with wires attatched. Then hook up new one, need to bend an optical sensor middle of board before installing new board into front cover so Just bend like the old one, also make note of LEDs because they need to fit into their individual positions. Just bend like old ones as well. Before you re-install front panel back-on heater housing and have the board installed in the front panel, make sure all the font cover push buttons click on and release, in other words return to position once you have actuated them. My board had a slight bend in it and would not allow one of the push switches to actuate as it was jammed into actuated position and would not release due to the bend in the PCB of the board. I simply backed off two of the mounting screws allowing the PCB to float just a bit allowing the buttons to actuate and release like they should. Not a big deal in leaving the PCB a little loose as it will not be going anywhere once you complete the installation.At first I was a little disappointed with the cycling action of the heater once it was installed. But what I did not take into account was that the heater needed to cycle to sense the correct room temp for the new board and after 4-6hrsit was back working great. Don't be surprised if you show a different number of LEDs lit with the new board compared to your old one due to temp sensing differences from one board to the next.Overall I like these heaters. They work great to Supplement your houses main heat source. I have mine against an inside wall pointed toward my main entrance to the house. After owning it for about five years I know for a fact it is saving me $30-$40 per month depending on the price of home heating oil. When oil was 4.65per gal, I was saving well over $50-$60 a month. I live in Alaska for what its worth and it runs/cycles 12months out of every year, and might get turned totally off for a total of 2weeks out of those 12months.", "EdenPure's first heater endorsed by Bob Villa.  They no longer make this model which is over ten years old.  This model is reliable and energy efficient and safe in the home.  It has rollers and can be moved from room to room is necessary.  Heat is constant and comfortable.", 'Really like these heaters as this is my 2nd one. Very safe around pets and kids as there are no hot surfaces and it is whisper quiet. The remote control is very handy also.', 'Very fast shipment part was dead on easy to install and works great thanks. A+++', 'Works very well ', 'All I can say is that I love it!', 'Love this small heater box , can be transported anywhere ', 'This product was a gift to a disabled family member.  Its performance and ease of use demonstrate that this was a good buy as well as a wise choice.  I heartily recommend this heater. ', 'easy to install, saved me $200.00', 'Would be better if it had a thermostat ']

Title: Mr. Heater MH18B Propane Heater Red
Reviews: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don’t aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]
