Title: DAYTON Portable Electric Jobsite  3VU36
Reviews: ["I'm currently on my 3rd Dayton  heater, all the same model, over two winters. Iuse it for heating an attached greenhouse with double pane glass, dimensions14 x 25' and a story and a half tall.  I live in Duluth, MN with temps thatcan easily get down to -20 to -30.  All that being said, the heater does a goodjob keeping the greenhouse at 60 degrees with temps -20.  The first one lastedonly weeks before a short circuiting (?) problem, and I exchanged for a new oneunder the one year warrenty.  The second one only lasted a few days on it's second winter when the heating element no longer functioned, though the fan still did run.  I exchanged that one under a Square Trade warrenty and so farit has worked well.  Keep in mind the heater runs on 220 volts, so depending onwhat you pay for electricity your monthly costs can add up.  I would alsorecommend keeping it out of very humid conditions, and I always remove it fromthe greenhouse when watering and for several hours after until the greenhousehas dried out a bit.  I think it would work very well for a garage or detachedbuilding.  Just don't know if it is as rugged as I would want, but perhaps things are built nowdays as being more disposable.  Regardless, I would make sure you have a warrenty to protect yourself.", 'I bought this little heater to heat my 24 x 24 semi-insulated workshop. The walls are insulated, but the ceiling is just 1/2 inch plywood with no insulation. When I first unpacked the Dayton 3VU36, I was skeptical because of its size. Boy was I fooled.First run - Garage temp was 34 degrees (23 degrees outside with ice on the ground). Within 15 minutes, there was an increase of 14 degrees in the shop area. At 30 minutes, there was an increase of 22 degrees total (shop temp 56 degrees).The noise level is no different that the little box fan that I run in the summer. Not bad at all.Overall, I am a little shocked as to how well it is actually working. I would definately recommend it to a friend or family member. However..... I think it might struggle a little if used in an uninsulated area.', 'Used more to dry the moisture out of the air after warming with a torpedo propane heater in my shop.  Good to use for small area as main heat. Quiet for a 220 heater.', 'If you are serious about heating, and I mean really heating, your garage or shop, then a 240 volt heater is the way to go.  The 110 volt cheap heaters only produce about 1500 watts on maximum.  This 240 volt heater produces 5600 watts.  You do the math! It is necessary to wire a 240 volt outlet into your system but worth the trouble.', 'love the Heater', 'works well for the price, we use it to keep a greenhouse above 60 degrees in the winter months with outside temps at or around 8 degrees. This does a good job and worth the $99 investment.', 'Good unit as a temporary (part time) heater. Used to heat a two stall garage space while working on a car.Does require an electricial to run a 220 service to plug in the heater.A little noisy but does throw heat.', "I'm going into my fourth heater in 4 years. They only last a year or less and it's impossible to get parts. When they work, they're great. They just don't last."]

Title: Mr. Heater MH18B 18000 BTU Hunting Big Buddy Portable Propane Gas Heater, Grey
Reviews: ['Chose M18B no fan.  Heater gives out immediate heat, warms body AND air! Fast!Opted to NOT pay for another RV furnace repair.  BIG BUDDY fuel efficient, love it!', "It's not a good value because it does not have the fan on it.  I expected a fan to be present on the heater. Without the fan it will NOT sufficiently heat a space of 120 square feet.  With enough time it will heat it. However it has to be on high to do so and is a waste of propane. If it had the fan. It would sufficiently heat the space on low in a short amount of time.It is my opinion this heater is a waste of money without the fan.As far as quality. I believe the heater itself is of good quality.  It starts straight away. ", 'Mr Heater makes the best indoor/outdoor propane heaters; and as a professional guide of 40(+) years I use Mr. Heater Big Buddies in all my Whitewater/Fishing camps at this time of year... and you will find them at any reasonably accessible basecamp that I have set up for climbing/mountaineering projects in the winter as well.  ', "I returned it because it didn't have a fan on it to blow the heat with, but I have two of them, but with fans and they are very good heaters. Title: RARE VINTAGE - Victor Electric Products Inc. Metal Floor Heater H-1357 - TESTED
Reviews: ["I use this heater in my clinic and my patients absolutely love it. It's amazing how quickly it heats a room without air blasting or noise. It has a nice safety feature where it makes a horrible noise if it's tipping over (it only happens if I'm moving it when it's on). In fact several of my patients have gone out and bought their own for home. I should get a commission.", 'I have an old 1911 craftsman style house with no insulation.  My heating system is an outdated oil furnace.  As we all know the price of fuel is always fluctuating and seems like it is going to stay that way.  It costs me about $300.00 a month in the winter.  Which is ridiculous, especially when the heat just does not stay in the house for long.I needed a knew plan and changing out the heat system or insulating the house is not an option at this time.  So I went out and bought the presto heatdish.  It produces so much heat that during the winter I no longer had to heat the entire house to stay warm.  I would just carry the heatdish around with me, saving me hundreds of dollars month to month.  I had a few other electric heaters before I purchased this one and the difference is night and day.I  have had this heater for almost 3 years now and it still works as well as the day I purchased it.  It paid for itself in its first week work.  With as much use as this gets I would of expected it to burn out a while ago, but that is not the case.The drawbacks: It does not have an automatic turn off system if it were to fall over, but it does have an alarm that is unmistakably loud.   There is also a footlight that you cannot turn off or on, but you can just take out the lightbulb if that bothers you.Great product and highly recommended. Thanks for reading.', "Proven, ancient technology that outperforms the daylights of newer, highly rated products. It's effective (heats the room quickly and thoroughly), efficient (only 1,000 watts), safe (automatic shut-off features), and built to last. Sometimes a product cannot be improved upon.  ", 'It gives off a good amount of heat but it has one big design flaw where the dish can not be tilted. This means the dish is in a fixed position which points into the air slightly. So if the surface you place it on is taller than you are while seated you will struggle to feel it. The safety tip over buzzer also prevents you from sliding something underneath it to tilt it yourself.', "This is a wonderful heater.  I am a smoker and visit my family a lot.  I choose to smoke in the garage there and my sister in law bought this for me to use in the garage. It warms up quickly for the immediate area and it doesn't take long for the surrounding areas to warm up either. Once this gets going I don't even need a coat.  (Ohio area)  I have a house with very tall ceilings in the master bedroom and living area.  In the winter this little heater warms up quickly, even going right to the high setting.  I always have to turn it way back too.  I am widowed now and I don't need to keep the entire house warm, just where I am.  I do recommend this.  Oh, it is safe, if you move it at all when it is on you get a loud buzz sound!  If on the fence about it I would go with it.", 'Great price, lightweight, energy efficient. It has worked very well so far. The price was the best I found on Ebay. I think the design is very good. The shape of the dish plus the shiny interior helps it be much more efficient than a regular space heater. It gets very hot very fast. It also has a buzzer in case it tips over. A great all around heater to warm a person up fast.', "These are fabulous heaters (radiant warmth, like the sun) and are in great condition.At first they didn't quite meet my needs, because I needed them to point straight ahead, whereas they are angled slightly upward and this is not adjustable. However, I set each heater on a slanted platform (which I made out of heavy cardboard), and now they meet my needs perfectly. (Parabolic heat dish heaters warm whatever is directly in front of them, within about, say, 15 feet.) You won't believe how much glowing warmth they put out!Also, Rob was great to do business with.", "I live in a 1920's craftsman style house with poor insulation. This heater is wonderful and has allowed me to turn my thermostat down several degrees and still be comfortable here in Minnesota. I would give it 4 1/2 stars if I could because it is actually a little bit large to walk around in a small house with small rooms.  But that said, even set as low as it will go, it still puts out a lot of heat. In fact, I have to be careful not to put it in a room near my thermostat because the furnace will not come on at all if I do!  I have already recommended it to friends.", 'This heat dish pumps out heat so intensely it’s like a dryer for your cloths if sitting in front of it. I could feel it’s radiant heat from about 15ft away. Wayyyy better than other heat dish I had no contest. It does not oscillate and no remote only 2 features not on this probably because it is heavy duty. This is the best heat dish, look no further. ', "I had a socially distanced bourbon tasting party for four on my back patio during January 2021 in Chicago. My neighbor had two of the Presto dishes so I ordered two more. Even though the evening's temperature dipped into the mid-20s, all four of us were completely comfortable sitting in our patio chairs with a our own Presto dish to keep us warm. The next day I ordered two more dishes to complete my set."]

Title: 2 Pack - Portable Buddy Heater, 4000/9000-BTU -F232050
Reviews: ["I bought this heater for my small garage workshop. My electric heater kept tripping the breaker while using other equipment. I was afraid of other gas heaters due to their carbon monoxide emissions. This was one of the few gas heaters rated for indoor use. It also has an oxygen depletion detector and tip over cut off feature which I thought was very important.This heater silently keeps my shop warm in even the coldest temperatures and can also be attached to a 20 pound propane tank with an accessory hose ~ which I also purchased. I've run this heater for up to 6 hours uninterrupted with no noticeable fumes and since all the heat is focused out the front, it can be set close to a wall with no worries.I know I'm going to get a lot of use out of this heater. It was a very reasonable price and filled my needs perfectly. Highly recomend the Mr. Heater Buddy for heating small spaces.", 'Here in Monterey County the weather can be colder in the evenings. At my home we cut of the central heating back in ‘88 so we all dress up like eskimos to keep warm. Don’t get me wrong. We do use electric heaters in certain areas but after purchasing this Portable Propane heater, it was Heaven sent. I recommend this product with all my heart. It is compact. It is durable. It is easy to refuel. It is warm to hot. And now, as we speak, the 5 ft extension hose just arrived. When connected from my Gas Buddy to a 20 lb propane tank, I should get at least 24 hrs of constant heat. Thank you for your time. ', 'The last power outage we only had kerosene heaters.  They are big, bulky, heavy, require pouring fuel and the fumes left us wheezing and coughing.  Therefore, we found these Mr. Heater, bought two and what a difference.  Small enough to be moved from room to room and so much safer.  You will love Mr Heater.', "Small and practical for portable heat when equipped with a disposable bottle, it's even great for a more permanent heat source - just pair this heater up with a hose and a large refillable propane bottle.  It even has a pilot light for easy on and off use.  Two heat settings, 4000 and 9000 BTUs.  The back of the heater stays cool to the touch, so it can be used backed against a wall.  Six stars for this heater.", 'Really nice heater. Relatively easy to operate and has safety features. Heater will not run all night, though with the small propane cylinders. ', "Love this portable propane heater. Can't wait to take it camping. In the meantime, we use it around the house to warm up and enjoy the heat it produces. If the power goes out, we will stay warm with this heater!", "This is a very good product.  What is different about Mr. Heater compared to other small heaters is that it uses 1 lb. propane tanks, thus it does not have to be plugged in or placed near an electrical outlet.  It is easy to use and have a anti tip safety feature that will cut the unit off if the unit is tipped.  Keep on hand a few 1 lb. propane cylinders, and you're good to go.  Very good heater for small spaces and can be used indoors.", 'Great propane heater with 2 settings. I also bought a 12ft hose to connect to a 5 Gallon propane tank. The low setting was enough to warm my 29ft motor home. Perfect.', 'Purchased the additional Mr. Heater 10\' hose (item F273704) that you don\'t have to use a filter and connected it to a 20 lb. bottle of propane.   Easy to light and ran all night on low to keep my greenhouse warm.  I used a 1.5" PVC water pipe and ran the pipe under the foundation of my greenhouse and then ran the hose through it outside where the tank was located.  For safety reasons, you aren\'t supposed to have the 20 lb. tank inside near the heater.  I cut up an old wash cloth and stuck it inside the pvc pipe to keep bugs and cold air from entering into my greenhouse. So easy to do.  ', 'Product operates exactly as advertised, which nowadays is not always the case. It functions easily and simply. Really like the option to go to larger capacity tank for longer use periods or not having to change out bottles constantly.']

Title: 【Dyson】"AM04 Hot + Cool Heater/Table Fan" Good condition confirmed operation
Reviews: ["Because of  a Great Price offer  so I thought Id try The Dyson AM04as I have nothing but praise for their Vacuum cleaners.   Its not big enough to really cool off a room and its too big to be a desk fan so just keep dimensions in mind when ordering.I like the fan as a Heater more then I like it as a Cool Fan but that's my opinion.I do like that its able to be both a hot and cool fan depending on time of year in one machine.if you think because its a dyson and its expensive you will get a Heater that Burns you or a Cool Fan that will Blast Artic air until you are content, you might be setting yourself up for disappointment.           If sheer Blasting power of either hot air or cool air is what you seek my opinion is Dyson falls Short and cheaper models are available, with more power.I enjoy the bladeless design and having both in one machine and for the price I'm happy!", 'This product does a great job in a living room on those hot summer days and cold winter nights. The heating function works exceptionally well and automatically holds the room temperature. The fan operation is true to Dyson standards and creates a smooth calm flow of air throughout the room. I definitely am glad that i purchased this unit used since a new unit costs about $400. Way too much for a fan. I am defiantly happy i purchased this second hand.', 'I have always wanted a Dyson hybrid fan and heater and when I saw an opportunity to get it for less than $300, even at refurbished condition, I had to just get it. It IS supposed to be refurbished by a Dyson certified dealer so I felt I could trust its condition to be satisfactory and safe. So far, the fan has been great in circulating air, albeit a little noisy even at its low setting, but it IS a fan and to be expected. I have not experienced using the heat setting yet, although I have tested it to be working so hopefully it will be sufficient for the winter months. Has a few dings, but its cosmetic and all I really care about is that it is safe to use, especially around children.', "Dyson produces high quality products that can have a problem once in a while so the company reworks the product and sells it at a more attractive price. I've had the hot and cool fan just a few weeks and it's working just fine. It's especially quiet, heats up and cools down quickly, and the remote makes it really easy to control. I also like not needing a separate fan and heater.", 'Fan works great, the remote makes it better. The heater is not as warm as most electric heaters, but will warm things if left on for a while. Saves having two separate devices. Was refurbished, but looks good and nicely packaged for shipment.', 'We used it on our sail boat.  So far just the summer.  It appears the heater works better than the cool.  but it is way better that not having!', "This fan/heater moves a lot of air in fan mode, and heats up quickly (however it takes about 20 seconds for the heating element and fan to switch on once the heater is engaged).It's probably a little quieter than most fans that move this much air, but it's not as whisper quiet as the new Dyson models. Even on the the lowest fan setting it could be considered a good sleeping noise maker. As advertised mine did not come with a remote, but I ordered one off the Dyson website and it works perfectly. I'm a big fan of this fan. 4/5 stars only because it's a little louder than I expected, but aside from that I LOVE IT.", 'I also have a brand new version so I can compare versions that are 5 apart and honestly there is very little difference from one to the other. I think we should all keep that in mind when considering the possibility of getting a newer version.  It is amazing how close to each other they are in function. Truly amazing.', 'High quality materials, high performance.', "I have wanted this Dyson fan for 6 years,but couldn't afford it. When I saw it on sale I didn't  hesitate and ordered  it. I am extremely  thankful  it came  early,as we were hit with a heat wave that lasted ten days at 110 degrees."]

Title: Dr Infrared Heater DR-122 Bedbug Heater with Thermometer and Timer, Big, Black
Reviews: ["The unit was easy to assemble and we had it quickly up and running in 20 minutes. The quality of components and hardware is good and the instructions were easy to follow. The deciding factor in purchasing this unit was that it ran off of one 110v outlet. Other units that we looked at required multiple circuits (one required 4).In regard to negative feedback, it is nominal but the S clips that hold the center racks in place are very loose and it would be nice if Dr. Infrared would design them a little bit more rigid. The temp gauge/meter is of good quality but you need to understand that the timer counts back and not forward as to how long the unit has been on.We deal with bed bugs daily at our men's homeless shelter and it is so nice to take their belongings and quickly bake the little buggers out in under two hours. We are seriously thinking about getting a couple more tents in the near future.", "Although I am grateful for a solution that doesn't cost thousands of dollars I have three complaints about this bed bug heater:1. The instructions are cursory, especially given how concerned most users will be to do things correctly, and the diagrams for assembly are faint. A link to a video would be great.2. The hooks to hold the shelves on WILL NOT fit in half the holes pre-drilled in the poles. And I mean WILL NOT with the force of two adults twisting and grunting in awkward physical positions. The holes are simply inadequately made. Note that I did get the other half in, so it is not that I cannot figure out how to do it, although a better diagram and an explanation would have helped see complaint #1.3. It takes HOURS to heat up to 120F and it's a really hot summer here! Would have been nice to know that. See #1.A minor disappointment is that the timer has no presets. A huge design bonus would be if the thermometre-timer could shut off the heater at the appropriate time. One really has to monitor over a period of hours, and can't using it overnight.", 'Does the job well, easy set up. You can put so much inside and price was cheaper than most.', 'TOOK SOME TIME TO FIGURE OUT THE SEQUENCE TO PUT TOGETHER.  ONCE WE RE-ASSEMBLED IT A COUPLE OF TIMES IT ALL CAME TOGETHER.', "Worked one time and wouldn't turn on again after that.", 'Everything top  notch', 'POOR']

Title: Dr. Heater DR218-3000W Greenhouse Garage Workshop Infrared Heater 3000-watt
Reviews: ["Bought this for my workshop in the winter.  It's only 12x12 but has very tall ceilings so I needed something that could heat the space adequately.  The unit is a lot smaller than I thought so that was a plus as it doesn't take up much room.You will need a 220V outlet which I had.  It doesn't heat the room super quick. The controls work well and so far it seems like a decent unit for the price.", "I originally bought this to heat my wife's greenhouse replacing two milk house heaters. Once the plug had been replaced, it fit perfectly into our Electrician installed electrical box.The heater works really well, and we\'re very pleased with it.   However.... having to deal with a "retro-fit" before we could even get the heater plugged in was very disappointing, and caused quite a delay.', "A lot better than milkbox heaters. Great heater for the money.A+A+A+', 'Perfect heater for my small work shop and model train layout.  It puts outmore than enough heat on cold winter days.  Thanks for a great product design.', 'Have not had to use yet but looks good and heats well.  Will know more when gets cold enough to need heat in greenhouse.', 'Works great', 'This heater heats very quickly.  It is designed to heat a greenhouse.']

Title: Mr. Heater 60,000 BTU Portable Propane Forced Air Heater, 50% Quieter
Reviews: ['This Mr Heater is great.  I use it in a 1000 sqft shop and it warms it up in minutes.  I replaced a radiant kerosene heater and am glad I did.  Years ago I had a kerosene tube heater that was extremely loud but the Mr Heater is very quiet.  Highly recommend.', 'I am convinced ALL Mr Heater products are nothing buy JUNK!  Lights right up first time - worked for about 20 minutes.2nd use - lights right up - runs for 10 minutes shuts off - Re-light -works for 10 minutes - shuts off TRIED to re-light - no dice - boxed it back up and sent it back,This is not the first Mr Heater item I have had issue with -They use to make a quality product - something changed - LGB!', 'Dont heat up as everyone say. Ran it about an hour in my garage at 32f didnt get much warmer, maybe to 34 in an hour with door closed. Smelled like burned propane and my eyes were burning, had to shut it off it was so bad. Looks to me that people that review them on YouTube are people that sell them. Will be selling this heater get something electric. Would not recommend at all, i was very disappointed. ', 'Had it on low setting and thawed out all my frozen water pipes in a 2 bay garage that was under 10 degrees F. ', 'I recommend this heater.  It works well and heats up my shop quickly and easily.', 'This thing heats my garage in less than 5 minutes. I very impressed. Very happy with this purchase.', 'Great to use in a garage environment.', 'Good little heater. 400 sq foot garage. Gets it up to 80 easy.  , I have to turn it off to keep from sweating!! They should make them more efficient. A little costly if used a lot.', 'Set up is a cinch. Physical was smaller than expect which was a plus. ', 'compact works great will take the chill out of 1200 square feet shop']

Title: 6,000 - 18,000 BTU Portable Radiant Propane Heater
Reviews: ['I\'ve wrestled with the heating options for my sun room since my wife and daughter through out my "old" kerosene heaters.  I considered the small propane table top heaters but my wife nixed that idea.  The typical outdoor 8 foot high propane heaters would have probably have drawn to much oxygen from the 13\' X 20\' sun room.  As I searched for other heating options, I came across this heater that stored a 20 lb. tank and made it look aesthetically pleasing.  It provides the right amount of heat for various atmospheric conditions!', 'We use the heater to supplement our fuel oil furnace. Works great to give a shot of heat while maintaining an overall lower temperature while we are gone', 'We got the heater shortly before Christmas 2017 here in Texas. Same day it arrived we had a freeze. Heater was installed in a converted barn and temp got up to about 75 in 15min or so. We have been using it for about a week now in below freezing temps with no issues other than it takes a few clicks to get the pilot to light. With all 3 burners going I pointed my temp gun at the front. My gun only goes to 1,000 deg and the heater is over that.', "Great heater for my garage/workshop.  The heater puts out enough heat to warm up my 24' x x24' garage on a cold winters day (in Michigan).  With it's 3 settings (Lo, Med & Hi) I start on Hi to raise the temp, then I set it to Lo to maintain temp.  I like the idea that the LP tank is built into the heater (instead of a separate tank and extension hose).  It makes the heater easy to roll around the shop and set it where the heat is needed.  I've had no issues with it not starting or operating properly.All in all, this is one great little portable heater.  I'd definitely but it again.", 'It is exactly what we needed. Works great and heats fast. Great product.', 'It is used every day sometimes three or four times to take the chill off in my 14 x 30 cabin. Fifteen min. or so is all it takes even when it is 12 fa outside. Wish I had it last year. Thanks Mr Heater !', "I've had this heater for a month now and have used it in my garage. It works great in the garage even when it was 20 degrees outside. On high, I have to sit about 2 feet away or I start to get too hot. I normally turn it to medium setting once I start getting hot. It takes about 5 minutes to get up to full heat, and very minimum fumes.  I'm still using my first tank of gas! I love this heater!", 'This heater holds a 20-pound propane tank. It does a good job of providing radiant heat. The pilot light ignites automatically, making the heater easy to use. I am happy with it, although I have used it only three times so far.', 'fast shipping and heats up the area we needed it for quit fast', 'Works great, Gives off perfect amount of heat with the three settings.Recommended to anyone that is cold, and on a budget for heat.I first learned of these while in Greece in the navy. we used them over winter, where the climate was not so cold, but, you still needed something for quick heat to take the chill off.']

Title: Mr. Heater 60,000 BTU Portable Propane Forced Air Heater, 50% Quieter
Reviews: ['This Mr Heater is great.  I use it in a 1000 sqft shop and it warms it up in minutes.  I replaced a radiant kerosene heater and am glad I did.  Years ago I had a kerosene tube heater that was extremely loud but the Mr Heater is very quiet.  Highly recommend.', 'I am convinced ALL Mr Heater products are nothing buy JUNK!  Lights right up first time - worked for about 20 minutes.2nd use - lights right up - runs for 10 minutes shuts off - Re-light -works for 10 minutes - shuts off TRIED to re-light - no dice - boxed it back up and sent it back,This is not the first Mr Heater item I have had issue with -They use to make a quality product - something changed - LGB!', 'Dont heat up as everyone say. Ran it about an hour in my garage at 32f didnt get much warmer, maybe to 34 in an hour with door closed. Smelled like burned propane and my eyes were burning, had to shut it off it was so bad. Looks to me that people that review them on YouTube are people that sell them. Will be selling this heater get something electric. Would not recommend at all, i was very disappointed. ', 'Had it on low setting and thawed out all my frozen water pipes in a 2 bay garage that was under 10 degrees F. ', 'I recommend this heater.  It works well and heats up my shop quickly and easily.', 'This thing heats my garage in less than 5 minutes. I very impressed. Very happy with this purchase.', 'Great to use in a garage environment.', 'Good little heater. 400 sq foot garage. Gets it up to 80 easy.  , I have to turn it off to keep from sweating!! They should make them more efficient. A little costly if used a lot.', 'Set up is a cinch. Physical was smaller than expect which was a plus.  It is a bit noisy; but it raised the temperature in my 750 ft2 shop 30 degrees within a couple of hours. I will be getting another one for my garage and home. ', 'compact works great will take the chill out of 1200 square feet shop']

Title: 6,000 - 18,000 BTU Portable Radiant Propane Heater
Reviews: ['I\'ve wrestled with the heating options for my sun room since my wife and daughter through out my "old" kerosene heaters.  I considered the small propane table top heaters but my wife nixed that idea.  The typical outdoor 8 foot high propane heaters would have probably have drawn to much oxygen from the 13\' X 20\' sun room.  As I searched for other heating options, I came across this heater that stored a 20 lb. tank and made it look aesthetically pleasing.  It provides the right amount of heat for various atmospheric conditions!', 'We use the heater to supplement our fuel oil furnace. Works great to give a shot of heat while maintaining an overall lower temperature while we are gone', 'We got the heater shortly before Christmas 2017 here in Texas. Same day it arrived we had a freeze. Heater was installed in a converted barn and temp got up to about 75 in 15min or so. We have been using it for about a week now in below freezing temps with no issues other than it takes a few clicks to get the pilot to light. With all 3 burners going I pointed my temp gun at the front. My gun only goes to 1,000 deg and the heater is over that.', "Great heater for my garage/workshop.  The heater puts out enough heat to warm up my 24' x x24' garage on a cold winters day (in Michigan).  With it's 3 settings (Lo, Med & Hi) I start on Hi to raise the temp, then I set it to Lo to maintain temp.  I like the idea that the LP tank is built into the heater (instead of a separate tank and extension hose).  It makes the heater easy to roll around the shop and set it where the heat is needed.  I've had no issues with it not starting or operating properly.All in all, this is one great little portable heater.  I'd definitely but it again.", 'It is exactly what we needed. Works great and heats fast. Great product.', 'It is used every day sometimes three or four times to take the chill off in my 14 x 30 cabin. Fifteen min. or so is all it takes even when it is 12 fa outside. Wish I had it last year. Thanks Mr Heater !', "I've had this heater for a month now and have used it in my garage. It works great in the garage even when it was 20 degrees outside. On high, I have to sit about 2 feet away or I start to get too hot. I normally turn it to medium setting once I start getting hot. It takes about 5 minutes to get up to full heat, and very minimum fumes.  I'm still using my first tank of gas! I love this heater!", 'This heater holds a 20-pound propane tank. It does a good job of providing radiant heat. The pilot light ignites automatically, making the heater easy to use. I am happy with it, although I have used it only three times so far.', 'fast shipping and heats up the area we needed it for quit fast', 'Works great, Gives off perfect amount of heat with the three settings.Recommended to anyone that is cold, and on a budget for heat.I first learned of these while in Greece in the navy. we used them over winter, where the climate was not so cold, but, you still needed something for quick heat to take the chill off.']

Title: Dr. Heater DR218-3000W Greenhouse Garage Workshop Infrared Heater 3000-watt
Reviews: ["Bought this for my workshop in the winter.  It's only 12x12 but has very tall ceilings so I needed something that could heat the space adequately.  The unit is a lot smaller than I thought so that was a plus as it doesn't take up much room.You will need a 220V outlet which I had.  It doesn't heat the room super quick.  I usually turn it on 30 minutes before I'm going to work out there and it's good enough.  Can't expect much more from a unit so small.  The controls work well and so far it seems like a decent unit for the price.", "I originally bought this to heat my wife's greenhouse replacing two milk house heaters. This heater warmed her10x14 greenhouse so well and evenly that we don't need a second heater anymore and she had new growthon plants in the middle of last winter with snow on the ground. I liked it so well I bought another one for my work shop.", 'THE PLUG ABSOLUTELY WOULD NOT FIT INTO A STANDARD USA ELECTRICAL BOX ! ! ! !We really wanted the heater to be ready for the arrival of cold weather, and it was a huge shock to have to deal with re-fitting / re-placing the plug before we could get the heater and our Greenhouse ready.We had to competely replace the plug !     Once the plug had been replaced, it fit perfectly into our Electrician installed electrical box.The heater works really well, and we\'re very pleased with it.   However.... having to deal with a "retro-fit" before we could even get the heater plugged in was very disappointing, and caused quite a delay.', "A lot better than milkbox heaters. Got it late in the season ,Early Feb. I have an uninsulated 10x12 greenhouse and when it got down to 18 it kept it at set 50 degrees.. Didn't run as much as the milkbox unit.  . Havent got my electric bill yet so cant fully rate it and also hasent gone thru Dec. and Jan.", 'Great little heater, plugs into our 20 amp outlet for window ac. Puts out way more heat than our 110 volt infrared heaters, hope its easier on the electric bill??.  Once we have our outside wood boiler hooked up, this little heater will be used in the green house. Great heater for the money.A+A+A+', 'Perfect heater for my small work shop and model train layout.  It puts outmore than enough heat on cold winter days.  Thanks for a great product design.', 'Have not had to use yet but looks good and heats well.  Will know more when gets cold enough to need heat in greenhouse.', 'Works great', 'This heater heats very quickly.  It is designed to heat a greenhouse.']
